This course explores the practical uses of information systems and technology (IS/IT) in both home and professional contexts, giving a foundational understanding of the field. It includes hardware, software, networks, internet technologies, communication, multimedia, graphics, and system applications, among other facets of IS/IT. The curriculum has a strong emphasis on practical learning through lab sessions, which make up a sizable portion of the coursework and cover productivity tools and PC installation. Students should be able to identify key IS/IT applications and components with ease by the end of the course, as well as have a firm grasp of their functions.
